  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "三国志英傑伝は、光栄の戦略シリーズ「三国志」を基にしたスピンオフ作品で、戦いの中での主要キャラクターに焦点を当てています。ゲームは、複数の兵士ユニットを用いた戦略的なバトルと、劉備が町を訪れ、NPCと話し合い、新しい装備を購入し、軍隊のために新兵を勧誘する「アドベンチャー」モードの間で時間を分けています。\n\nバトル中、プレイヤーは戦闘に連れて行くユニットを選択します（劉備のような主要キャラクターは必須です）し、敵ユニットとの小競り合いを行います。戦闘やアドベンチャーモードでのプレイヤーの選択によって、物語が分岐し、異なる戦闘を経験することができます。",
      "lang": "ja",
      "source": "romu"
    },
    {
      "text": "The Super Famicom port of \"Sangokushi Eiketsuden\", a Strategy game, published by Koei, which was released in Japan in 1995.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "igdb"
    },
    {
      "text": "In the 3rd century AD, the powerful warlord Liu Bei accompanied by his blood brothers Guan Yu and Zhang Fei, begins to raise an army to battle his way across China to ultimately obtain the title of Emperor, and restore the Han dynasty.\n\nThroughout the story-driven campaign, the player will have to win 64 battles. Each battle has its own victory condition within a turn limit. The player will need to wisely allocate soldiers of multiple types and devise strategies to overwhelm an opposing army. Every garrison of soldiers are led by their own officers. The chosen battles will determine the outcome of the campaign and how the story advances.\n\nIn between battles there are settlements where information can be obtained from citizens, shops that sell weapons and items to enhance the player's soldiers, and Liu Bei can meet with his officers to formulate plans for the next move.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "igdb_storyline"
    },
